### Habitability API Tests
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5219/api
@authToken = 

### 1. Login to get authentication token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Evaluate single planet habitability (Planet ID 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/evaluate/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Get factor scores for a planet (Planet ID 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/scores/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Rank all accessible planets by habitability
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/rank
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Find most habitable planet
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/most-habitable
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Batch evaluate multiple planets
POST {{baseUrl}}/habitability/evaluate-batch
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

[1, 2, 3]

### 7. Test with invalid planet ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/evaluate/999
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 8. Test without authentication (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/habitability/evaluate/1

### 9. Get all planets to see what's available
GET {{baseUrl}}/planets
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
